What do we call the study of legendary creatures like the Loch Ness,

90
00:05:11,760 --> 00:05:14,160
Monster, Bigfoot and Unicorns?

91
00:05:14,160 --> 00:05:20,320
Is it a crypto-zoology, b, proto-zoology, or c, paleo-zoology?

92
00:05:21,120 --> 00:05:22,720
You knew the answer to this, didn't you?

93
00:05:22,720 --> 00:05:23,600
I did. Yes.

94
00:05:23,600 --> 00:05:27,680
If you look back at our archive to September 2008,

95
00:05:27,680 --> 00:05:32,160
you will find an episode all about a crypto-zoology.

96
00:05:32,160 --> 00:05:32,800
Well done.

97
00:05:32,800 --> 00:05:35,840
If you got that right, particularly if you remember that program.

98
00:05:36,399 --> 00:05:42,319
Now, vocabulary from this program, there was enchanted to talk about a time when magic was

99
00:05:42,319 --> 00:05:43,679
believed to be real.

100
00:05:43,679 --> 00:05:48,879
A feat is something that is very difficult to achieve, and a panacea is a cure.

101
00:05:48,879 --> 00:05:51,679
Something that's potent is strong and powerful.

102
00:05:51,679 --> 00:05:54,239
And if you deploy something, you use it.

103
00:05:54,239 --> 00:05:56,000
You put it into operation.

104
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:58,159
And something pressing is urgent.

105
